               <note resp="additions_0">Mss. Koprulu 766, undated but written in the lifetime of IA by Muhammad b. Abdallah al-Tamimi al-Mahdawi Similar to Chapters 462-553 in Futuhat, but clearly an earlier version, with less elaboration and poetry. A close comparison of the handwriting shows that Tamimi is also the scribe for the texts of (stolen) Yusuf Aga 4868, which OY and others have ascribed to IA (eg Hilyat al-abdal) From SH</note>
